The Prophet Abacuk, in like manner, crieth out againſt couetous rich men: who by briberie and corruptition; 
                        Abac. 2 by crueltie and oppreſſion; enriched themſelues: woe to him that coueteth an euill couetouſnes to his owne houſe, that he may ſet his neaſt on high, to eſcape from the power of euill. Thou haſt conſulted ſhame to thine owne

